main event: A single gray-white flying saucer was observed rotating on its axis and flying at a slow speed over the ocean near Newport Beach, California on July 9, 1955.
interesting points: The object was estimated to be 2,000 feet above the ocean.
The object disappeared into a cloud.
The Air Force's 4602d Air Intelligence Service Squadron was instructed to conduct a limited follow-up investigation, but no follow-up report was received.
The case was carried as 'Insufficient Data for Evaluation'.
The observer's report did not include any photographs of the object.
